The paper deals with secure multi-party computation, which is a central problem in cryptography. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of communication protocols, which falls under the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of producing samples from a desired distribution, which could be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
